<article id="post-2807" class="post-2807 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-careers category-costa-rica category-family category-general tag-moving">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2010/12/a-year-in-canada/" rel="bookmark">A year in Canada</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<div>
A year ago tonight, my family returned to Canada from Costa Rica. We had lived abroad for a year and a half, and had done our best to make a go of a new life in a new country. But it wasn&#8217;t to be, and we finally came to the reality that we had to move back home.<br />
So, a year ago, we packed up a highly uncomfortable hour of the morning, boarded our airplane, and spend nearly 16 hours travelling north. We arrived late in the evening, with an irate kitty, to the most amazing -18C weather I&#8217;d ever felt. Within days, we&#8217;d tried to reinsert ourselves into a society that we&#8217;d &#8212; at last in some part &#8212; tried to forget.<br />
A year later, I&#8217;m starting to forget that we ever left.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2010/12/a-year-in-canada/#more-2807" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;A year in Canada&#8221;</span></a></div>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
